Composition and medical‑use coverage for zebularine as a hypomethylating agent, especially in oncology, autoimmunity, and transplant tolerance, is densely prosecuted.

Several families tie zebularine to IDO, immune tolerance, radiosensitization, and demethylation‑driven re‑expression of silenced genes (e.g., p16), leaving little room to recite these mechanisms broadly without running into prior art.

High‑level “epigenetics + regeneration” concept:

Patents around histone methylation in cardiac regeneration, HDAC inhibitors in dental pulp, and demethylating agents as immunotherapy adjuncts make it hard to claim the general idea of “epigenetic modulation to improve tissue repair” as new.

Where it looks “blue” (open / defensible)
Topical zebularine‑class formulations for skin and wound healing

